From 3c4774e45611ab86cacb6a0d459876d00d797faf Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Vincenzo Grimaldi <vincenzo@igrimaldi.engineering>
Date: Mon, 6 Jul 2026 13:57:36 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] fix(arm-library): grounded floor, conveyor feed, boxes no
 longer vanish
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

- Animation is now state-driven (useState placedCount): the arm places each
  box once and parks when the build completes. Removes the modulo loop that
  made it re-grab box 0 forever and made placed boxes flicker/disappear.
- Add an infeed conveyor (belt, rails, legs) with the next real cartons queued
  and advancing as they are picked.
- Add a professional floor: drei <Grid> technical grid over a dark ground
  plane, plus scene fog for depth — replaces the bare floating plane.
- Add a Replay control (remounts via nonce) since the build no longer loops.

Still schematic geometry (no CAD/GLB). Typecheck clean; parity PASS; no engine
change.
---
 web/app/arm-library/page.tsx         | 30 ++++++++++-
 web/components/demos/ProfiledArm.tsx | 78 +++++++++++++++++++---------
 2 files changed, 82 insertions(+), 26 deletions(-)

